http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: Example encoding density and magnetic susceptibility for some Rock-Material Classes. The rock material in a formation is an instance of the material class that is 'partOf' the 'body' of that kind of material in the re-gion, which is also an instance of the material class. E.g. the wacke con-stituent in the Tezzeron Sequence is an instance of gsrm:Wacke that is part of the 'wacke in British Columbia', which is an instance of gsrm:Wacke.
